“I can’t wait for everyone to see [season 2 of #Euphoria]. … I felt like I was back in my other skin almost. I felt like I was going home to this really fucked-up home. … I’m really enjoying and learning more about Cassie and seeing her grow. It’s been a lot of fun,” @sydney_sweeney gives us a glimpse into the highly-anticipated second season of @euphoria and more at the link in bio.

node.text:
No matter what role she's playing, @sydney_sweeney has written a book for it. “I have 100-page journals on each of my characters… I literally build from the hospital, from the day they’re born, and the daycare that they go to," she says. It's with this thoughtful approach that we get emotional performances on-screen from Sweeney time and time again. “The reason we sit a certain way or we look at a person a certain way, it all comes from some memory from our past that we may not be able to put our finger on. But it’s what made us who we are today." Read more from the actress in our August cover story at the link in bio.

node.text:
There's levels to @sydney_sweeney. Perhaps best known for her roles as an angsty, emotional, and disturbed teen in #Euphoria and #TheWhiteLotus, she's also an avid reader, spends her time optioning books for her own production company, and is a mechanic, casually rebuilding a 1969 Ford Bronco these days—how's that for unexpected? We talk what's next for the 23-year-old actress and producer in our August cover story at the link in bio.
